Objective: Optimization of a material energy landscape

tspan.tspan: to find favourable and stable configurations

text.tspan: Problems: High-dimensional search space, costly quantum
mechanical calculations, forbidden regions add constraints
Approach: Constructing a multi-fidelity model to incorporate
information from inexpensive but less accurate calculations
to accelerate the optimization of the energy landscape
Our goal is to combine atomistic simulators with different costs & accuracies
to reduce the computational cost for global minimum inference
Multi-fidelity models can be built via Intrinsic Model of Coregionalization
(ICM) [2]: ICM assumes a linear dependency of the fidelities and enables
information exchange between correlated fidelities to reduce the
uncertainty over the shared search space
ICM adds new kernel hyperparameters, corresponding to the correlations
